               <msContents>
                  <summary>Mahzor according to the Eastern Ashkenazi rite for the whole year</summary>
                  <msItem> 
                     <title type="desc" xml:lang="he">מחזור מנהג אשכנז המזרחי לכל השנה</title>
                     <title type="desc" xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Maḥzor minhag Ashkenaz ha-mizraḥi le-khol ha-shanah</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
                  </msItem>                  
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc>
                        <support>parchment</support>
                        <extent>ff. 461</extent>
                        <collation><locus>Fols. 1-2</locus> are a later addition.</collation>
                     </supportDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <summary>Ashkenazic square script</summary>
                     <handNote><persName>Jacob ben Gershom</persName> pointed the MS. The vocaliser's colophon on <locus>fol. 23</locus> is at the end of a quire (<locus>fols. 17-24</locus>), which must originally have been placed at the end of the codex, containing Song of Songs, Ruth, and Ecclesiastes. The name <persName>Aaron</persName>, which must have been that of the scribe, is pointed out (<locus>fols. 31r, 85r</locus>).</handNote>
                  </handDesc>

